# .gitleaksignore — SHA-256 fingerprint allowlist for Gitleaks
#
# This file lists findings that are intentional, well-known default
# credentials for a local-only lab stack.  They are documented in
# README.md and .env.example as requiring replacement before any
# non-local deployment.
#
# Path- and regex-based allowlist rules are configured in .gitleaks.toml.
# Add SHA-256 fingerprints here when `gitleaks detect` reports a finding
# you have verified as a known false positive:
#
#   gitleaks detect --report-format json --report-path findings.json
#   # Copy the "Fingerprint" field value from each false-positive entry
#   # in findings.json and paste it below, with a descriptive comment.
#
# ─── Known default credentials covered by .gitleaks.toml allowlist rules ──────
#
#   File              Variable / key                  Default value   Reason
#   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   .env.example      GRAFANA_ADMIN_USER              admin           Grafana local default; documented to change
#   .env.example      GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD          grafana         Grafana local default; documented to change
#   docker-compose.yml GF_SECURITY_ADMIN_PASSWORD     ${VAR:-grafana} Inherits .env.example default
#
# ─── Fingerprints ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# (Add SHA-256 fingerprints from `gitleaks detect` output here as needed.)
